children.subject:
Asking because Schedule Planner says "208 of 208 reserved seats filled for requirement: Electrical Engineering & Computer Science (EECS), EECS/NE, EECS/MSE or L&S Computer Science major".

If that's true and there's only 208 seats total, then I never had a chance of getting in in the first place.
Does this mean that there will be more than 208 total seats in the class?

history.content:
I was 44th on the waitlist for CS 162 this morning with 50 seats open in the class. I assumed I would get in once they started letting people in. However, now I'm 31st on the waitlist, and the class is full. I am a non-major, but I thought the reserved seats were already filled. Besides, I thought those didn't matter for adjustment period anyway.

What up? And is it likely I can still get in?

EDIT: I'm in section 102 btw, which is one of the ones that are still open.
